urlLink The Nation Oily decision? : "Before leaving office, Bill Clinton made permanent a  temporary ban on building roads, harvesting timber, mining  for ore or prospecting for oil and gas in a vast swath of  remote, federally-owned woodlands. The so-called 'roadless rule' --  adopted after two years of study by the US Forest Service --  protected an area equal to about 2 percent of the United  States, and including nearly a third of all of our forests. "